CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 18, 1960, pg. B7 reads: "10. The Coopers Brothers Inc., who furnished the background music for the style show, and some of the entertainment, with their smooth and sweet-toned stereo hi-fi. They also donated the organ for the wedding ceremony.  This booth was represented by Jack Cooper and assistant Charles Tyler."
TitMainTitle: Jack Cooper and Charles Tyler standing with piano, organ, and stereo in Cooper Brothers Incorporated booth in Syria Mosque for the 1960 Courier-WAMO Home-A-Rama
